Get ready to be transported to a delicious happy place thanks to tonight's riff on classic chili verde. You'll simmer cumin- and garlic-seasoned ground turkey and hearty cannellini beans with our spicy-tangy green salsa, and serve it all over with buttery rice with a dollop of sour cream for creamy tanginess. A final flourish of fresh chopped cilantro adds herbaceous green contrast. Grab a big spoon and get comfy with this cozy, satisfying bowl of goodness.

== White Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @White Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of
@salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is
tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Prep ==

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Roughly chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

== Chili Verde ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat.
Add @Ground Turkey{10%ounce}, garlic, and @Cumin{1%tsp}; season with @salt and
@Pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until turkey is browned and
cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @Green Salsa{7.06%ounce}, @Cannellini Beans{1%can} and their liquid, half
the cilantro, and @water{1/4%cup}. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring
occasionally, until flavors meld and chili has thickened slightly, ~{5-7%minutes}.
Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in @Butter{1%tbsp}.

Divide chili verde and rice between #bowls{} in separate sections. Dollop with
@sour cream{1.5%tbsp} and garnish with remaining cilantro. Serve.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.